About:

eindexer is an ad-hoc text indexing engine written entirely in Erlang. It was originally designed to index edoc files for erlware, but is capable of being used as a general purpose text retrieval engine.

Running:

$ sinan shell                             
1> application:start(eindexer).
ok
2> eindexer:index(text_files, "/home/tristan/Documents/org-mode").
ok
3> eindexer:run_query ("chatyeo languages IIT").
[{"/home/tristan/Documents/org-mode/bio",2.772588722239781},
 {"/home/tristan/Documents/org-mode/main.org",
  1.3862943611198906}]
4>
